FeedPackage.Description: Test database loader facility
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Questo progetto è stato creato per facilitare la creazione di basi dati di test. Generalmente creare basi dati di test è un'operazione lunga e ripetitiva. Con questo applicativo è possibile inserire i dati esportati in formato JSON dal db di sviluppo in un altro database creato ad-hoc. Il nuovo database avrà struttura identica al database di origine e conterrà solo i dati che servono ai test di integrazione con il database. Questa fase è rieseguibile più volte: il database di test, se presente, viene eliminato, creato e ricaricato con i dati previsti dal developer.
FeedPackage.Summary: Creato per facilitare la creazione di basi dati di test.
FeedPackage.Tags: Dapper Dapper.SimpleCRUD clabnet postgresql test data Npgsql
FeedPackage.Title: DataTestLoader

FeedPackage.Description: Test database loader facility
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
To obtain Integration Test effective and consistent, these must always be performed in isolated environments, in order to ensure the existence of the expected data and to ensure the possibility to modify them if necessary.
Unfortunately, the creation of databases for tests is an activity time-consuming and repetitive. This project was created to facilitate the creation of database test.
The idea is simple: the data is exported from the development database based on .json format and then recreated in another database created ad-hoc. The new database will have an identical structure to source database and will contain only the data you need to test. This can be reproduced several times, since the test database, if any, is deleted, created and loaded with all data provided by the developer.
FeedPackage.Summary: Automatically creation and loading Postgresql database test data for integration tests
FeedPackage.Tags: Dapper Dapper.SimpleCRUD postgresql test data Npgsql
FeedPackage.Title: DataTestLoader

This is useful if some of the server variables have sensitive data that you don't want to log.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Added RaygunClient.ApplicationVersion property. * Added convenient RaygunClient.Attach method for WinRT and Window Phone. * Improved stack trace information for WinRT and Windows Phone. * Additional WinRT and Windows Phone state information in error reports.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Removed Bluetooth permission requirement from Xamarin.Android provider.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Can now specify IgnoreFormDataNames in config file. * Improved stack trace for Xamarin.Android. * Removed unused android permission: access external storage.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * The IgnoredFormNames feature will now filter out cookies which now have their own section in the request data. * When enabling Raygun4Net via the http module, the new excludeErrorsFromLocal option on RaygunSettings can be set to true to prevent any exceptions being logged from your debug/dev environment. * Corrected the window width/height values in the Raygun4Net provider.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Added RaygunClient.SendingMessage event to the main .Net provider. This can be used to make final modifications to the message, or to cancel the send operation. * Added IRaygunApplication which can be used to provide a custom RaygunClient to the HttpModule. * If a windows phone is connected to the internet, but fails to send a message, it will be saved to the device to send later.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Raygun can now send exceptions in an MVC application that is using a HandleErrorAttribute to suppress page crashes. * Resolved a duplicate key exception when creating the cookies list to send. * Added RaygunClient.ProxyCredentials property.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Prevent sending exception logs multiple times.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Avoid sending duplicate exceptions. * Resolved a NRE in WinRT.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * ignoreFormDataNames has been removed and replaced with 4 separate options: ignoreFormFieldNames, ignoreHeaderNames, ignoreCookieNames and ignoreServerVariableNames. * Setting one of these new options to * will prevent any value from that category from being sent to Raygun.io. * Placing * before, after or at both ends of an ignored key will be used as an ends-with, starts-with or contains condition. * The RaygunClient methods that accepted IEnumerables have been changed to be multi-parameter methods. * Added RaygunClient.UserInfo property, and RaygunIdentifierMessage.IsAnonymous property. * All obsolete members from the previous version have been removed.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Support for FtpWebResponse to resolve a cast exception.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Support for Windows Store apps (Windows 8.1 and Windows Phone 8.1)
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Support for WebApi (Use the RaygunWebApiClient.Attach method). * RaygunClient.RemoveWrapperExceptions method. * Can now send null exceptions rather than crashing.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * All Raygun4Net providers now have a SendingMessage event that can be used to either cancel a send, or make any last second modifications to the message before it is sent to Raygun. * Improved the SendInBackground methods. * Added a null check for WebRequest.DefaultWebProxy
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Resolved a bug reading the request data when calling SendInBackground. * Some improvements to the SendInBackground function for WebApi projects. * Resolved a potential bug when reading request.InputStream. * Improvements to getting the IP address. * Resolved a couple of minor regressions in the JSON serialization. * Improvements to better support AggregateException by sending all inner exception details.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Resolved issue when serializing strings containing certain control-characters.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * While serializing the message, catch exceptions that can occur when getting property values. e.g. The ScopeId property of an IPAddress object. * Improved the performance of getting the processor name and OS version on older machines (i.e. Windows Server 2003)
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Moved MVC and WebApi support out of this package into their own packages to resolve dependency issues. (If you need MVC or WebApi support, see the Raygun4Net.Mvc or/and Raygun4Net.WebApi packages). * Removed redundant and unused message properties. * Wrapper exception list is no longer static to resolve a potential threading issue. * Resolved an issue sending exceptions on older versions of Android. (API level 8). * Message builder logic has been moved out of the message objects into separate builder classes. Keep this in mind if you instantiate your own Raygun message objects entirely from scratch - you may want to use the builder classes to perform the default value population.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Better serialization of dictionaries with non-string keys. (This improves custom data display for all providers, and resolves a critical bug in Xamarin.iOS). * Resolved an issue when trying to flag exceptions as "Already sent by Raygun" that have non-string key Data dictionaries. * Catch and send exceptions that occur in custom SendingMessage event handlers. * Prevent Xamarin.Android provider double-sending some exceptions. * Resolved potential issue when serializing exceptions in WinRT. * RaygunSettings class is no longer read only.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Support for Xamarin.iOS unified API. * Automatically send anonymous user info from Xamarin apps to at least track the user impact of each exception. * isRawDataIgnored option in web.config for .NET projects to never send the RawData of web requests. * Send and SendInBackground overloads to send user information - useful for heavy threading scenarios where setting the user info on the RaygunClient isn't ideal.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Native iOS error reporting for both classic and unified API (Enabled using a new Attach overload). * Property to provide a custom IWebProxy * ApplicationVersion property on RaygunSettings to set easily. * When stripping AggregateException, send all inner exceptions. * AggregateException support in all applicable providers.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Raygun.io Provider for .NET Framework + Windows Store apps, WinRT, Windows Phone and Xamarin
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Support for cyclic object structures when sending custom data. * Raygun for the iOS Unified API now works on ARMv7s architecture. * try/catch exceptions when getting the IP address which can cause problems in WCF error handlers.
FeedPackage.Title: Mindscape.Raygun4Net

FeedPackage.Description: Working with dates and time in .NET works great, but I feel it could be more natural to work with them. new DateTime(2000, 6, 3) is less natural than 3.June(2000), isn't it?
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Have a look at DateApi.Tests/Overview.cs in the source code, to get a feeling for how the api works!
FeedPackage.Summary: The DateTime and Timespan Structs of the .net framework are somewhat awkward to work with, this api helps to make code more readable, for example: var today = 23.February(1990).At(3.AM());

FeedPackage.Description:
A JavaScript Date object to add much better parsing, internationalization support, and all the functions and syntactic sugar you could wish for.
Date JS was started by Geoffrey McGill in 2007, he abandoned it on May 13th 2008; leaving the Google Code repository stagnant and with many bugs unresolved.
This fork was started improve and maintain DateJS. To keep what is still the most full featured JavaScript Date library alive, maintained, and improved. Currently we're on track towards a 1.0 release - having fixed almost all the existing bugs and added several new features, improved parsing, and many other changes.
